A Parliamentary committee yesterday turned away two officials of Kenya Power and directed CEO Ken Tarus to appear before it next Tuesday. They will explain the high cost of power and procurement malpractice. The National Assembly Energy committee turned away GMs Peter Mungai and Charles Cheruiyot, saying only Tarus can respond to the queries. “It is unfortunate that the managing director is away on a different assignment. As a committee we are concerned it is the second time he has not come,” committee chairman David Gikaria said at Continental House, Nairobi. Click here for more political news